From: Cisco IOS Configuration Fundamentals Command Reference
FuncDef: To end the current configuration session and return to privileged EXEC mode, use the **end** command in global configuration mode.

ParaDef.Info: This commmand has no arguments or keywords.

Examples: In the following example, the end command is used to exit from ALPS ASCU configuration mode and return to privileged EXEC mode. A show command is used in privileged EXEC mode to verify the configuration.
ExtraInfo: This command will bring you back to privileged EXEC mode regardless of what configuration mode or configuration submode you are in.![](/c/dam/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif)---**Note** ![](/c/dam/en/us/td/i/templates/blank.gif)This global configuration command can be used in any configuration mode.---Use this command when you are done configuring the system and you want to return to EXEC mode to perform verification steps.

RelatedCmds.description: Exits from the current configuration mode.
